TUNIS, Tunisia, February 12, 2019/APO Group/ -- 
                                                        
                            The African Rugby Confederation will hold its elective General Assembly on Saturday, March 2, 2019 in Marrakech, Morocco.


                                It should also be noted that the governing Ministry endorsed this candidacy during a hearing granted by the Secretary of State for Sport Mr AHMED GAALOUL
                            

For this purpose, Tunisia will present its candidacy for the presidency of this continental body of the rugby world, represented by Mr KHALED BABBOU the current vice president of the Tunisian Federation of Rugby and member of the African Confederation of this discipline.



It should also be noted that the governing Ministry endorsed this candidacy during a hearing granted by the Secretary of State for Sport Mr AHMED GAALOUL to the candidate KHALED BABBOU and to the president of the F.T.R AREF BELKHIRIA